HEADWORD: Sesspool
<hw>Sess"pool`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prov. E.
<ets>suss</ets> hogwash, <ets>soss</ets> a dirty mess, a puddle + E.
<ets>pool</ets> a puddle; cf. Gael. <ets>ses</ets> a coarse mess.]</ety>
<def>Same as <er>Cesspool</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

